{"body": "Maybe -- my gut feeling is that since this doesn't break the previous style of usage, at all, it's a net positive.\n\nI don't have time to write up additional code examples, but I'm thinking that developers of engines may find it useful.\n\nAt the very least, it allows us to intelligently select the controller (and therefore, associated view files, and on down the line) that handles the comment functionality, without having to use a separate concern, reducing the working vocabulary of the application reflected in the routes file to only the level of detail necessary.", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/7936990", "created_at": "2012-08-22T14:59:42Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/7422#issuecomment-7936990", "updated_at": "2012-08-22T15:00:23Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 7422, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ernie/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ernie/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ernie/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/ernie", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ernie/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/ernie", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ernie/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://0.gravatar.com/avatar/2274a7476f6d2ac7aedcdec0651d0542?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F6a600c968f4e6a843dcaf600c1694e42.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ernie/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ernie/received_events", "gravatar_id": "2274a7476f6d2ac7aedcdec0651d0542", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ernie/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "ernie", "type": "User", "id": 14947, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ernie/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "5237fbc3bd3543c15100b86b"}, "id": 7936990, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/7422"}
